Wytheville.

Clinch River Veneer Co. v. Kurth & als. July 2d, 1891. Appeal Dismissed as Impbovidently Awarded. Appeals from two decrees of the circuit court of Washington county, rendered June 21st, and October 18th, 1889, respectively, in a chancery cause therein pending, wherein the Clinch River Veneer Company and others are complainants and Charles Kurth and others are defendants. A. H. Blanchard, for appellants. Fulkerson, Page Hurt, for appellees. Rauntleroy, J.,

delivered the opinion of the court.

We are of opinion that the appeal in this case was improvidently awarded; and to dismiss the same.

Appeal dismissed.
